# Enterprise Active Directory Infrastructure Lab

## Overview

This project demonstrates the design, deployment, administration, hardening, and troubleshooting of a Windows Server enterprise environment using Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS). The lab simulates a production-grade corporate infrastructure with redundant domain controllers, centralized identity management, DNS/DHCP services, Group Policy enforcement, and disaster recovery operations.

The environment focuses on real-world enterprise administration and SOC-aligned operational skills, including identity management, detection engineering readiness, infrastructure resilience, and incident-level troubleshooting across Windows Server ecosystems.

---

## Objectives

- Deploy a fully functional Active Directory enterprise domain
- Configure multiple redundant domain controllers for high availability
- Implement DNS and DHCP services in an enterprise network
- Design and enforce Group Policy Objects (GPOs)
- Validate Active Directory replication and SYSVOL synchronization
- Simulate enterprise-level infrastructure failures and troubleshooting
- Harden Windows Server environments using security best practices
- Automate administrative tasks using PowerShell
- Execute disaster recovery and rollback procedures
- Develop SOC-relevant troubleshooting and investigation skills

---

## Technologies Used

- Windows Server 2022 / Windows Server 2025
- Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)
- DNS (Domain Name System)
- DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)
- DFS Replication (DFSR)
- Group Policy Management Console (GPMC)
- PowerShell 5.1 / PowerShell 7+
- Hyper-V / VMware Workstation
- Windows Admin Center
- Microsoft Defender for Endpoint

---

## Lab Architecture

### Infrastructure Layout

| Server Name   | Role                        | IP Address     |
|---------------|----------------------------|----------------|
| DC01          | Primary Domain Controller  | 192.168.1.10   |
| DC02          | Secondary Domain Controller| 192.168.1.11   |
| WIN10-CLIENT  | Domain-Joined Workstation  | 192.168.1.100  |

---

## Network Configuration

### DNS Configuration

- Forward Lookup Zone configured for `company.local`
- Reverse Lookup Zone implemented for internal resolution
- Active Directory–integrated DNS replication enabled
- Conditional forwarding configured for external name resolution
- DNS health validation performed using diagnostic and resolution tests

### DHCP Configuration

- IPv4 scope configured for internal enterprise subnet
- DHCP reservations configured for infrastructure systems
- Lease duration optimized for lab environment simulation
- Dynamic DNS registration enabled for client devices

