## SYSVOL and DFS Replication

### DFSR Configuration

- SYSVOL replication configured across DC01 and DC02
- Replication health monitoring enabled
- DFSR event log analysis performed for validation
- Replication backlog checks executed during testing
- Synchronization consistency verified across domain controllers

### Troubleshooting Scenarios

Resolved simulated enterprise failures including:

- SYSVOL replication breakdown between domain controllers
- DFSR service state corruption and stalled replication
- Group Policy propagation failures across domain
- DNS replication inconsistencies affecting authentication
- Domain controller communication and trust issues

---

## Disaster Recovery Testing

### Recovery Scenarios Executed

- Domain controller failure and recovery simulation
- SYSVOL corruption and restoration
- DFSR non-authoritative synchronization rebuild
- Active Directory metadata cleanup procedures
- DNS service restoration and validation

### Validation Procedures

- Authentication functionality confirmed across domain
- Group Policy application verified on endpoints
- SYSVOL availability tested on all controllers
- Replication health validated using diagnostic tools

